i India|volume=|pages=53-57|isbn=9789387651166|issn=19302940|via=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.amazon.in/Satanic-Empire-Jernail-Singh-Anand/dp/9383755997|title=The Satanic Empire|publisher=Global Fraternity of Poets|year=2019|isbn=9789383755998|location=Gurgaon Haryana India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.amazon.in/Vocies-Void-Dr-J-Anand/dp/9383755865|title=VOICES FROM THE VOID|publisher=Global Fraternity of Poets|year=2019|isbn=9789383755875|location=Gurgaon Haryana India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://www.amazon.in/Indian-English-Spanning-Decades-Century/dp/8170196493|title=PAN INDIAN POETRY IN ENGLISH SPANNING FIRST TWO DECADES OF 21ST CENTURY|publisher=Today and Tomorrow's Printers and Publishers|year=2019|isbn=9788170196495|editor-last=Anand|editor-first=J S|location=New Delhi India|pages=|editor-last2=Chakraborti|editor-first2=Basudeb}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.amazon.in/FIGHTING-FLAMES-Dr-J-Anand/dp/9383755830|title=FIGHTING THE FLAMES|publisher=Global Fraternity of Poets|year=2019|isbn=9789383755837|location=Gurugram Haryana India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.amazon.in/BROKEN-NARRATIVE-JERNAIL-SINGH-ANAND/dp/B0849T7ZCW/ref=sr_1_6?qid=1585744205&refinements=p_27%3ADr+Jernail+Singh+Anand&s=books&sr=1-6|title=The Broken Narrative|publisher=YAYATI MADAN G GANDHI GROUP OF PUBLICATION|year=2020|isbn=9788194485827|location=Hisar Haryana India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|title=LILACS IN BLOOM|publisher=The Poetry Society of India|others=A Project of Galaxy International Foundation|year=2020|isbn=9789389213133|editor-last=Anand|editor-first=J S|location=Hisar Haryana India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|title=POETS & POETRY: SPACES WITHIN & WITHOUT|publisher=Earth Vision Publications|year=2020|isbn=9788194485841|editor-last=Anand|editor-first=J S|location=Gurugram Haryana India|pages=|editor-last2=Jaggi|editor-first2=Parneet}}\n*{{Cite book|title=DYNAMICS OF POETRY: THE SAID AND THE UNSAID|publisher=Earth Vision Publication|year=2020|isbn=9788194485872|editor-last=Anand|editor-first=J S|location=Gurugram Haryana India|pages=|editor-last2=Jaggi|editor-first2=Parneet}}\n\n==Major awards and recognition==\n*Member of the Commission for the International Best Poet Award 2017 of the World Nations Writers Union, Kazakhstan<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wnwu.org/index.php/en/|title=High Level Officials of THE WORLD NATION WRITERS UNION OF KAZAKHSTAN (WNWU)|last=Garrido|first=Carlos Hugo|date=2017-10-09|website=World Nation Writers' Union|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-07-12}}</ref>\n*First Ambassador of the World Union of Poets, Italy. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://atunispoetry.com/2016/04/25/world-union-of-poets-celebrates-the-power-of-poetry-aims-to-bring-a-revolution-in-the-consciousness-of-time-issued-by-dr-j-s-anand-ambassador-and-general-director-wup/|title=WORLD UNION OF POETS CELEBRATES THE POWER OF POETRY: AIMS TO BRING A REVOLUTION IN THE CONSCIOUSNESS OF TIME, ISSUED BY Dr. J.S. ANAND, AMBASSADOR AND GENERAL DIRECTOR WUP|last=BORTOLAZZI|first=SILVANO|date=2016-04-25|website=ATUNIS|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n*Chairperson of World Foundation for Peace, and Writers International Foundation<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/bathinda/poems-rediscover-island-called-self/216121.html|title=Poems rediscover \u2018island called self\u2019|date=1 April 2016|website=The Tribune}}</ref>\n*Dr Anand  evolved the theory of BIOTEXT in Literary Theory<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://atunispoetry.com/2017/10/11/j-s-anands-theory-of-biotext-and-critical-perspectives-on-his-poetic-and-spiritual-creed-first-edition-2016-by-dr-roghayeh-farsi-author-introduction/|title=J.S. Anand\u2019s Theory of Biotext And Critical Perspectives on His Poetic and Spiritual Creed (First Edition, 2016) /  By Dr Roghayeh Farsi (Author, Introduction)|date=2017-10-11|work=Galaktika Poetike  \"ATUNIS\"|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US}}</ref>\n*Cross for Peace for his Lifetime Achievement in the Field of Poetry and Peace by Wolrd Union of Poets. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/11-May-2016/pak-poet-to-get-cross-for-peace-award|title=Pak poet to get Cross for Peace Award|last=Ahmad|first=Israr|date=2016-05-11|website=The Nation|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n*2017: Art4peace award by Art4peace Foundation, Hollywood, USA\n*2017: World epitome of leadership award World Institute of Peace, Nigeria\n*2017: Honored with Lord of World Peace and Literature Award, conferred at India World Poetry Festival, held at Ramoji City, Hyderabad 13-14th Oct, 2017\n*Dr M S Randhawa Award for Promotion of Art & Culture of Punjab Conferred\n*2009: Recipient of Penguin Rising Personalities of India Award \n*2008: Best Educationist Award for the outstanding achievements in academics by National and International Compendium in New Delhi\n*Avantika educational excellence award by Sri Rajiv Gandhi Foundation Ratia\n*Founder President, Philosophique Poetica [De-Anand] - A Portal for Poetry, Art, Peace and Philosophy\n\n==Membership and appointments==\n*Member, Syndicate, Punjabi University, Patiala.\n*Fellow, Punjabi University, Patiala\n*Member, Board of Studies, Guru Kashi University, Talwandi Sabo\n*National Vice-president, International Human Rights Observatory [ihro]\n*Patron and Honorary Chief Editor: Symphony International \n*Life Member: [[United Writers' Association|United Writers Association]], Chennai\t\n*Chairman of the International Society of Poets\t\n*Chairman of the Sufi Arts Foundation\t\n*Member of the Association of Indian College Principals\t\n*Patron: Academic Earth Institute of Multi-studies\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Anand, Jernail Singh}}\n[[Category:Poets from Punjab, India]]\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=June 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jernail Singh Anand\n| image              = [[File:Jernail Singh Poet.png|250px]]\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date         = 1955\n| birth_place        = Ludhiana, Punjab\n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (DEATH date then BIRTH date)  -->\n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = [[Indian people|Indian]]\n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = Poet, Author, Philosopher, Spiritualist, Enviornmentalist\n| years_active       = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n}}\n\n'''Jernail Singh Anand''' is a poet.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://jamiededes.com/2017/10/19/dr-jernail-s-anand-poet-writing-in-the-virtual-world-by-aprilia-zank-ph-d/|title=\"Dr. Jernail S. Anand (Poet), Writing in the Virtual World\" by Aprilia Zank, Ph.D.|date=2017-10-19|work=THE POET BY DAY|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://verbumlandiart.com/dr-jernail-singh-anand-a-philosopher-of-language-life-and-literature-essay-of-italian-poetess-claudia-piccinno/|title=Dr JERNAIL SINGH ANAND \u2026.a philosopher of Language Life and Literature / Essay of Italian poetess Claudia Piccinno \u2013 VERBUMLANDIART|website=verbumlandiof Maharaja Ranjit Singh College, art.com|language=it-IT|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref> Anand has authored 65 books of English Poetry, fiction, [[non-fiction]] and spirituality.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://atunispoetry.com/2016/09/14/dr-jernail-s-anand/|title=Dr. Jernail S. ANAND|date=2016-09-14|work=Galaktika Poetike  \"ATUNIS\"|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bol.com/nl/p/a-million-destinies/9200000014175757/|title= A Million Destinies [Poems], Dr Jernail Singh Anand {{!}} 9781484831342 {{!}} Boeken|website=www.bol.com|language=nl-NL|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref> He was awarded a Ph. D. in English by Panjab University Chandigarh  in year 2000. He is a environmentalist and a column writer. He retired as Principal and is now on an Honorary Position of Professor Emeritus at Institute of European Roma Studies and Research, Crimes Against Humanity and International Law, Belgrade, Serbia. Dr Anand has co-innovated the theory of Bio-Text in Critical Theory along with an Iranian Scholar, Dr Roghaye Farsi. He Was President of The World Poetry Conference Organized in October 2019 in Bathinda Punjab, India. <ref>{{Cite book|last=Dayal,|first=Dr Deen|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dxlgDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT655&lpg=PT655&dq=%22Philosophique+Poetica%22&source=bl&ots=GCpzYSaWD7&sig=ACfU3U3O66uQMSyFz4yMX9ex1f6pCMN1hA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjSmb3fyvzjAhVSSX0KHRnyAlUQ6AEwDXoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=%22Philosophique%20Poetica%22&f=false|title=Complexion Based Discriminations: Global Insights|publisher=Notion Press|year=|isbn=9781643242323|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://atunispoetry.com/2019/07/01/world-poetry-conference-poet-in-the-service-of-mankind-philosophique-poetica-and-grand-productions-canada-world-poetry-conference-13th-and-14-th-october-2019/|title=World Poetry Conference: Poet in the service of mankind conference 13th and 14th October 2019|last=Agronsh|first=Agronsh|date=2019-07-01|website=ATUNIS|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-08-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldliterature.in/|title=Philosophique Poetica|last=Aggarwal|first=S|date=2019-08-12|website=World Literature India|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-08-12}}</ref>  \n\n==Early life and education==\nBorn in 1955 at [[Ludhiana, Punjab, India|Ludhiana, Punjab]] and grew up at native village Longowal in the Sangrur, Punjab, Anand graduated from Govt. College, Ludhiana, and earned his Masters in English Literature from [[Punjabi University]], [[Patiala]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://atunispoetry.com/2016/07/06/the-interview-of-dr-j-s-anand-with-the-turkish-tv-building-bridges/|title=The Interview of Dr J.S. Anand with the Turkish TV. Building Bridges.|date=2016-07-06|work=Galaktika Poetike \"ATUNIS\"|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US}}</ref> Punjab University, Chandigarh conferred on him degree of Doctor of Philosophy in 2000 for his work on mysticism in the poetry of [[Walt Whitman]] and [[Puran Singh|Prof. Puran Singh]].\n\n==Career==\nAnand began his career as Lecturer in English at [[Gujranwala Guru Nanak Khalsa College|GGN Khalsa College]], Ludhiana. Then he became the Principal at DAV College, Bathinda and served there for 10 years. He co-founded World Foundation for Peace and was National Vice-President of International Human Rights Observatory in 2013 .  In 2016, he was called by the World Union of Poets [Italy]  to serve as the President of the Jury of their 2016 awards.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boloji.com/articles/49111/beyond-life-beyond-death|title=Beyond Life Beyond Death  by Durga Patva|work=Boloji|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n\nHe represented India at the Kibatek 39 Poetry Festival organized by the Pablo Naruda Literary Association, Taranto, Italy held in February 2016. He represented India at the World Institute of Peace Nigeria organized World Peace Seminar in Nov. 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wnwu.org/index.php/en/our-members/188-chief-advisor-to-the-president-of-the-world-nations-writars-union-in-kazakhstan-on-contemporary-world-literature-3|title=Chief Advisor To The President of the World Nations Writars' Union in Kazakhstan on Contemporary World Literature|last=User|first=Super|website=www.wnwu.org|language=en-gb|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n\nDuring his career, he served on the Boards of educational societies including the Senate and Syndicate of [[Punjabi University]], and Board of Studies of [[Guru Kashi University]]. Anand has authored 60 books, published 120 articles, published various national and international anthologies, and has introduced poets by writing Review Articles and Forewords for their books.\n\n==Selected bibliography==\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/title/trespassers-a-novel/oclc/34851544?loc=|title=The trespassers : A Novel|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Writers Workshop Kolkata|year=1995|isbn=9788171898190|location=Kolkata|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books/about/Spare_Me_O_Lucifer.html?id=ON6uHAAACAAJ&redir_esc=y|title=Spare me, O Lucifer!: Poems|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Writers Workshop (Rebird)|year=2000|isbn=978-8175956940|location=Kolkata India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.isbns.co.tt/isbn/9788173413322/|title=THE SPLIT VISION|publisher=Indian Publisher Distributors|year=2004|isbn=9788173413322|location=New Delhi India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18100628-beyond-words-poems|title=Beyond Words [Poems]: A Psycho-Spiritual Odyssey Into the Post-Colonial Mindscape: A Psycho-Spiritual Odyssey Into the Post-Colonial Mindscape|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Createspace Independent Publishing Platform|year=2013|isbn=9781484097502|location=California US|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://my.justfiction-edition.com/catalog/details/store/fr/book/978-3-8454-4939-5/the-wolves-of-malwadi?search=the%20wolves%20of%20malwadi|title=The Wolves of Malwadi|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=JustFiction Edition|year=2013|isbn=9783845449395|location=Latvia EU|pages=}}\n*.{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.amazon.com/MONSTER-WITHIN-non-fiction-Postmodern-Politico-societal/dp/1490932879|title=The Monster Within: A Postmodern Critique of the Politico-societal living systems (2nd Ed.)|publisher=Createspace Independent Publishing Platform|year=2013|isbn=9781490932873|location=California US|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first=J S|url=https://www.amazon.in/BURNING-BRIGHT-029-J-S-Anand/dp/819258397X/ref=sr_1_7?dchild=1&qid=1585916334&refinements=p_27%3ADr+J+S+Anand&s=books&sr=1-7|title=BURNING BRIGHT|publisher=The Poetry Society of India|year=2013|isbn=9788192583976|location=Gurgaon Haryana India|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18208145-confessions-of-a-corpse|title=CONFESSIONS OF A CORPSE: FICTION AT WAR WITH REALITY|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Createspace Independent Publishing Platform|year=2013|isbn=9781490516745|location=California US|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/2013/20130601/battrib.htm#6|title=A MILLION DESTINIES [Poems]: Post-modern Text traversing the contingent and the transcendent|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform|year=2013|isbn=9781484831342|location=California US|pages=}}{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.com/Metamorphosis-Emerging-Constructs-formation-constructs/dp/3659410586|title=Metamorphosis: Emerging Cultural Constructs And English Proverbs: A study of ancient wisdom in the context of the emerging societal patterns and formation of new constructs|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=LAP LAMBERT Academic Publishing|year=2013|isbn=978-3659410581|location=Saarbrucken Germany|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.in/Bliss-Ultimate-Dr-J-S-Anand/dp/9386242125|title=BLISS: The Ultimate Magic|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform|year=2013|isbn=9789386242129|location=California US|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.com/BELONG-YOU-Spirituality-Dynamics-non-fiction/dp/1490995366|title=I BELONG TO YOU|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=Createspace Independent Publishing Platform|year=2013|isbn=9781490995366|location=California US|pages=}} \n*{{Cite book|url=https://www.flipkart.com/the-lost-bliss/p/itmecw8fjpzzjbcp|title=THE LOST BLISS|last=Anand|first=J S|publisher=The Poetry Society of India Gurgaon|year=2014|isbn=9789383888122|location=Gurgaon|pages=}}\n*{{Cite book|last=Anand|first